Package: AI4BayesCode
Title: Stateful Modular MCMC Building Blocks with AI-Friendly Skill Chain
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2026-06-24
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jungang", "Zou",
           email = "jungang.zou@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("AI4BayesCode contributors", role = "ctb"))
Description: Header-only C++ library for stateful, modular MCMC samplers
    that compose NUTS, joint NUTS, BART, Gibbs, RJMCMC, HMM, slice sampling,
    and variational inference blocks within a single Gibbs loop. Generated
    samplers expose a uniform 6-method R interface (step / get_current /
    set_current / predict_at / get_dag / get_history) plus an optional 7th
    method 'readapt_NUTS' for sequential / online learning workflows.
    Ships a 25-check validator skill chain that an AI agent can use when
    generating samplers from natural-language model descriptions. Bundles
    the runtime, 39 reference examples, and the skill corpus, plus
    natural-language-to-code generation via 'ai4bayescode_generate()'.
